Third-party components / runtime dependencies
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

The MIT license above covers ONLY the source code in this repository.

This project does NOT bundle or redistribute any third-party code. At runtime
it imports hardware libraries that are installed separately by the SunFounder
PiDog installer and are licensed under the GNU General Public License v3:

  - pidog      (SunFounder) - GPLv3
  - vilib      (SunFounder) - GPLv3
  - robot_hat  (SunFounder) - GPLv3

These libraries are NOT part of this repository, are NOT listed as
dependencies in pyproject.toml, and must be obtained from SunFounder. If you
redistribute a combined/installed system that includes those GPLv3 libraries,
the combined work as distributed may be subject to the terms of the GPLv3 for
those components. The code in this repository on its own remains under MIT.

Python dependencies declared in pyproject.toml are under permissive licenses
compatible with MIT:

  - PyYAML        - MIT
  - python-dotenv - BSD-3-Clause
  - openai        - Apache-2.0
  - webrtcvad     - MIT
  - vosk          - Apache-2.0
  - fastapi       - MIT
  - uvicorn       - BSD-3-Clause

The Vosk German speech model (vosk-model-small-de-0.15), downloaded at setup
time into models/, is licensed under Apache-2.0 by Alpha Cephei and is not
included in this repository.
